caption: asian food, yeah, very tasty. Great location to meet with friends. The service was friendly and sociable. It has a good atmosphere.
One of my fav places for asian food. Dropped in on Mon I think. The bill was well within reason for the quality.
A top scene for tasty Asian food. Cool place to meet and catch up with coworkers. Service is consistently above par. Menu is similar to a restaurant in Jacksonville I liked.

Zhongshan restaurant was fantastic. There are many fast food Chinese places to eat where you can get your regular panda-express order, but finding anything resembling authentic Chinese food can have you driving our of Baltimore and up to Silver Spring to Oriental East. I was incredibly excited to try any Dim Sum option in baltimore- and this one did not disappoint. Their dumplings, pork buns and leaf wrapped rice were all amazing and a full meal for 2 came to less than 30 dollars. I'll absolutely be a repeat customer.

Orders took time to cook even though business is slow there. They’re very short handed with only one waitress helping customers while greeting people at the front desk. Mapo tofu we ordered has gone bad already and it tasted really terrible. 2 stars to the only waitress who helped me with my takeout orders. She is nice and at least willing to help even though it takes back and forth from the front desk and the back kitchen.
The food is good but more people need to come here to make it more lively. It is BYOB
Authentic cuisine.  Roast duck was fresh as were ginger and scallion prawns. Table and bathroom could have been cleaner.
:( We arrived at 11 am and waited 40 mins for the food. Food is bad. Tea is disgusting.
I love the food at this place. Only thing is that it takes a while to get your food but the taste always makes up for that
No flavor
The beef and rice noodle was amazing. Staff was friendly and it was a great experience! I would come again.

They just have a few of dim sum food and they are not authentic at all. It tastes really weird. Fried noodle tastes fine, however we ordered lunch special but they charge us its regular price. Do not recommend this restaurant.

Service was great! I definitely won't complain about the service.  Food wise? No. One of the food items I ordered was crab rangoon and it was literally ONIONS and whatever cream it was there was no crab (nor do you even taste the crab) inside.  I love onions but it should've been "onion rangoon" rather than "crab rangoon". Pork steam bun was bland, pork sio mai was "ok", lo mein was bland also.  Do I recommend this place for food? No, I do not. There was also a bug that was crawling on the floor.  Did I scream? No. Should i have left? Probably so.  Will i go back? Nope. I've had better and real "authentic" chinese food.

I've been to some pretty subpar restaurants before. That being said, this one took the cake for most bland food as well as horrific service.  Waitress took it upon herself to blatantly ignore me when trying to order. Even after ordering, she threw the receipt at me. Still, trying to be a respectful human, I dealt with it. When the food arrived she didn't speak just slammed it on the table. When my son and I began to eat l, we looked at one another in disgust. All in all, nothing was enjoyable about the service or the food. There are better places to waste $34.

Food was okay but was not really a dim sum place as advertised ie no carts and had to order. Don't go on Sunday at 11am. They really are not ready to serve at that that time even though they are open.
Love going for their Shanghai juicy buns
The food feels authentic (as far as I can tell) and is also terrific. Don't listen to the other reviews—the service is rather unpretentious (not a negative in my opinion), but the food is great.
The best Chinese food ever,  only place I will eat Chinese food from.. very authentic.. do not let the looks of the building or the neighborhood fool you...
No frills! Not appealing and very empty. Only one eating.
Pleasant surprise!
It was quick for a sit down restaurant. The potstickers were awesome as was the combo chow mein. The Mongolian beef was rubbey. Service was good!
Great lunch spot.

I love reading the reviews saying this is the worst Chinese someone has ever had. First off, you're an idiot if you don't realize that this is as authentic as you can get. Secondly, that food you eat is definitely not Chinese. That said, the atmosphere isn't great. The service was fine but nothing spectacular. But honestly the food made up for all of that. I'm definitely going back again.
It smells bad and the waitress was not pleasant.  The food is so-so.
This place has dim sum and the food is legit - it is not your cookie cutter Chinese restaurant!  I usually go with carry out or delivery.

The food tasted pretty good and the service was great....but I won't ever go back because the environment is beyond weird. You can tell its family owned. Which is normally fine but I felt it was TOO home like. I guess you'll just have to go see for yourself. I can't even explain it.
Nastiest food I ever had waste of money.highly disappointed in this place called me a liar then wouldn't offer to fix the problem
Good food place a little dingy

(Translated by Google) To be honest, the location of Zhongshan Restaurant is not very good, at least for those who drive by car, it not only costs money to park in downtown (arrow parking next to it is 5 dollars an hour), but also bear the risk of smashing the car.  Compared with the other one I visited two days ago, it seemed a lot deserted here, and no one came at six o'clock. The decoration is quite satisfactory, not too cold, but not too delicate. Perhaps the only bright spot is the painting on the wall (Shanghe on the Qingming Festival?)  Older pop music plays in the background.  The price of the food seems a bit not cheap.  That being said, the dishes are really delicious. Scrambled eggs with shallots. After I haven't eaten scrambled eggs for a long time, I will still feel a little moved when I eat eggs again. The fish-flavored shredded pork looks a bit dark, but the taste is surprisingly good.  If you haven't tried it before, it is recommended to try it and you will not regret it. But if I want to come again later, I am less worried about parking and downtown security, and parking requires money, at least at night I dare not come over to eat alone.  (Original) 说实话，中山酒家的地理位置并不是很好，至少对于自驾来的人说在downtown停车不但要花钱（旁边的arrow parking 5刀1小时），而且要承受爱车被砸的风险。  跟前两天去的另一家 来比，这里显得冷清了很多，六点这个点还没人来。装修还算中规中矩吧，不能算太寒掺，但也没有太精致的感觉，也许唯一的亮点是墙上的画吧（清明上河图？）  背景放着比较老的流行乐。  菜价似乎 有点不便宜。  话虽这么说，但是做的菜确实挺好吃。小葱炒蛋，许久没吃炒鸡蛋的我再次吃到鸡蛋还是会有些感动的味道。鱼香肉丝看起来有点黑暗，但是味道却意外的好。  如果没来吃过的话很推荐来尝尝，不会后悔。但是之后要不要再来呢，我自己比较不放心停车和downtown 的治安，而且停车还要钱，至少在晚上我是不敢一个人过来吃的。

The appetite is not small and the taste is very American Chinese food.  (Original) 去华盛顿看樱花回程路过巴尔的摩，眼看过了饭点儿，就在地图上找了一家进去吃，饭量不小，味道很美国中餐。
Great lunch special
Not for sure what I just try to eat ,but it was not good .I have had better Chinese food out of the 7-11.....Don't eat there !!!!!

This review is for dim sums only.  I am a sucker for dim sums. This is one of the worst dim sums I have had in the US.  I would give a 3 star for delivery. The website said the delivery starts only at 6pm. I ordered around 4pm via yelp. I received a call from the restaurant asking if I want the food earlier and that they could deliver in an hour. I said yes. The actual delivery was right on.  One star for dim sum. I feel that the food is not tasty and poorly made. Also, the portion was not generous at all. For example, my order included chicken feet, a pretty standard menu item at dim sum restaurants. It came with 3 chicken feet. (Usually it is about 6 or even 7 feet at other dim sum places in my experience). I am also unimpressed with Beef Tripe with Ginger and Scallion, Hom Sui Gok,  Pumpkin Rice Cake and Roast Pork Lo Mein. I would give passing marks to Mini Sweet Rice with Lotus Leaves, Steamed Roasted Pork Buns and Steamed Shanghai Juicy Buns though. Another let down was they did not include chilly oil in the delivery. Maybe I should've asked for it specifically rather than assuming that it is standard.  I have had other chinese food items at this restaurant and think that they are ok. There is a possibility that I will come again but will never order dim sums again.

This place was amazing!! Definitely a spot to try. I was a little skeptical after reading some of the reviews but everything was amazing. The food was super fresh and tasted fantastic. The restaurant is family owned and the woman who made our food and brought it to us was super sweet. You could tell she took pride in her food. We were the only people eating when we went which is a shame. Definitely a gem in the ruff.
Clean great fresh tasting food and good service
A quick go to Chinese restaurant. Beef brisket veggies noodle soup is excellent, ask for xtra spicy.

We selected a variety of options including beef lo mein, beef balls, crab rangoons, egg drop soup and sweet rice.  They were all delicious and very authentic! Our waitress was very nice and attentive. We will be back again. Thank you!

Visited it from downtown on Sunday.  Found we were the only customer at 130pm.   Owner and staffs were chatting, and turned on the light and aircon right after we sat down.  It smelled mouldy in first 10mins ... we ordered some dimsums. The rice roll with shrimp was the best, I can guarantee this was freshly made and the rice was so good, not too stickly.  Shrimp dumpling tasted good too.  Environment and service brought down the overall rating...food was alrite...worth tobtry if you never had dimsum before,.it's the only restaurant you can taste canton.dim sum.

Really good Chinese food that's not at all greasy. I have only had better in San Francisco. Great flavor, meat that doesn't look barely edible, and great steamed pork buns and steamed dumplings. Best to call in an order and pick up, delivery takes a long time.

Extremely pleased! Food was excellent. Wonton soup was particularly good with plenty of meat and thinner noodles for the wontons and tasty greens (pork pieces would have been nice too though). Spring roll was delicious, albeit a bit greasy. Food had that authentic slightly vinegar flavor that's hard to find--yum. Waitress was almost too nice. Prices were probably a little too high.

I can't even give this place 1 star. Spent $70 + on delivery for dinner and not one thing was good. Egg drop was soured, crunchies - stale, spring roll very greasy, sesame chicken nasty and soured, loe main very garlicy, general tso - had to spit it out, hot n sour soup bad.
